Combine almonds and coconut in a small skillet and toast over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes until golden. Transfer nuts and coconut to a plate to cool. Combine berries into a bowl with sugar and let stand 10 minutes. Add a few spoonfuls of the berries to dessert cups. Add 1/2 cup Dannon(R) yogurt to each cup, another layer of berries, then 1/2 cup more yogurt. Top dessert cups with toasted almonds and coconut and serve.